Review based on just the crepes, dragonfruit bowl and the lavender lemonade - My friend and I tried the Teriyaki Chicken Crepe and the Chipotle Chicken Crepe, we both thought they were overly sweet and did not have enough/ any chicken in the crepe at all. My friend had the dragonfruit bowl and enjoyed it but thought the lavender lemonade was quite average. I'll try the flavoured coffees at another time and update my review. Both staff and people in the store practiced social distancing!
This place is a gem. Loved it

I am giving it one star for a few reasons. I was so excited to come across this place ! I was intrigued by the menu, and when I walked in, I loved the esthetics. I was looking for somewhere to enjoy a treat, relax and read. This seemed like the perfect place. It’s very cozy and fun looking inside.The energy was so off in the place, it had a very dead vibe. I ignored it and went right up to the counter to order and started talking to the guy working. I came very excited and cheerful and sweet, and he was just blah. I asked how long they had been here, and he said he honestly didn’t know. Ok, he may have been new, but I don’t think that was  the case, but I may be wrong. He answered with no personality or tried to engage in conversation. He asked me what I wanted, and I said I would please like the Matcha chocolate strawberry thing, he said what? Like he had no idea so I repeated it and used cone this time instead of thing. It’s the only item with those ingredients so Maybe he’s new or just didn’t hear me, but I don’t think that was it. So then asked me if I wanted anything else, I said no thank you. Paid, and that was it. No personality or customer service at all. Didn’t tell me it would be ready in a few minutes, nothing at all. I had also mentioned it was my first time there and just got nothing from this person. So I waited and tried finding a spot. I felt like I waited forever, and I was the only one in there who had ordered, it was slow. So I finally get it by it being called out, and this woman also had no personality. Very dead energy and very weird vibes. There was also a back room, I had found and wanted to look at. A guy was standing in the there, and I had been polite asking if this space was opened. He said no unless you’re with the private party. I said o no, I was just looking around it’s my first time here. This room looks awesome, may I peak really quick, and he said yes, but his vibe was off and he said ugh, I just washed the floors. I could see that, and understand there was a private event happening soon, so I was trying to be respectful and understanding, I literally took 3 small steps from where I was already standing and he freaked out, even after saying I could. Thought it was so odd and off putting. So, I sit down to eat my treat and this is definitely the MAJOR REASON FOR THIS REVIEW. Thankfully I am not allergic to nuts, but this is a SERIOUS ISSUE! So as I stated I ordered the Matcha Chocolate Strawberry rice cone. No where in the list of ingredients did it mention almond slices. So I was very shocked to bite into my treat and get pieces of almond. Which I personally didn’t care for being mixed in with the flavors. I didn’t like them, but most importantly I was unaware of them. The person didn’t ask me if I have a nut allergy or mention it was part of that item, and the menu didn’t specify that either. So please fix that because if I was allergic to nuts, that would’ve been bad. Also, for the $ amount of the item ,l the strawberries  were sliced so thin, and not many of them, you didn’t get to really taste them, and you basically are left with the rice cone mostly. So more strawberries & thicker would perfect the treat. Lastly, I got there just before 7pm, they say they close at 8pm. I got my treat at 7:04 pm and basically right after I received me treat, they yell out they were closing. I double checked the time and it had an hour left. That was disappointing. I stayed and ate my treat and there were others inside as well still. No thanks for coming on the way out Overall, the experience was awful for my first time there. This is a long review, but I have spent 18 years in the service industry, and have loved every moment of what I do. Customer service is a top priority, it is a reflection of your business and what makes or breaks a place. So that’s heavily disappointing especially because the place is so well done design wise. The menu discrepancy is HUGELY IMPORTANT. I truly mean this review with the best intentions to help make aware of things that could be improved to help your business. ❤️
Good coffee, fun ambiance
Amazing coffee shop.Must visit if you are in Chicago.

Chipotle chicken! Yummy!!!

This coffee shop is a must for coffee lovers! Bru has a cute, cozy ambiance and good service. I spent some time there studying and still stop by for coffee or a sandwich even though I moved. They often have little free smoothie samples which are delicious!
Amazing!
Great place with amazing coffee. I like it:)

They had a small selection of snacks but I think that's because the area is so condensed. They had all the favorites like popcorn, nachos, candy, and ice cream. The girl behind the register was very friendly and welcoming. The recliner chairs are clean and comfy, too. I look forward to visiting here again!
Cozy spot with delicious drinks. The white chocolate lavender mocha was excellent.
I used to go here a few years ago and loved it. I recently went for the first time in years and the service was laughably poor. Too bad, but won't be returning again.
Love this place.  Plenty of tables, seating and electrical sockets.  Friendly customer service.  Cozy atmosphere and great for studying or reading a book.
cozy seating options and a super convenient printing service that saved me a trip to the print shop!

The cafe is beautiful, large and the food is an extensive variation of food and beverages. The first time I came with a friend, my coffee was forgotten twice over 25ish minutes. I went back and forth about 5 times. I know it was forgotten because I went over and the staff believed there were no more orders. Maybe a lost ticket. Didn’t bother me too much. Someone tried to give me a banana for it, nice, maybe if you are to offer at all, allow to give coffee instead next time ( I’m not assuming this is a customer facing issue) Then I went back a few times for for some tea lattes. No issue. Then, one day, I come back for two sandwhiches. A swarm of people were there that came in after us.  The two women in front of us took really long to order, adding little things here and there, changing their minds, didn’t know what they wanted. Maybe the front register person can usher them along or let them know they can look and come back immediately after they make up their minds or Maybe have 1 person come quickly to take the next peoples orders. Those customers took a very long time, as if they were talking from a stream of consciousness with no awareness of environment, not exaggerating. Anyway, this isn’t to judge them but just to point out that customer ordering with no bru control caused a backup, in my opinion. After that, the sandwhiches took a long time and a side of fruit was forgotten, Not a big deal but I could tell there are some issues with the flow of things. Maybe 1 person short in the kitchen. Bru needs to streamline things and keep them at a healthy, fast pace when the customers are coming. I don’t think this is about individual workers, I think it’s a system thing. Like maybe 1 more person to float around and help with random things... make coffee, pack that bag, give me the bread, refill the such and such. The people who work here are very very nice and need to convey to customers a sense of order. Otherwise, customers will harass them. I waited around for my sandwhich in front of the coffee makers for about 10 minutes after sitting and waiting for a while 1) other customers don’t need to be exposed to that conflict 2) poor workers.  just  needs to go faster. Maybe too many options? Honestly, I like it and the space is so big, many people just come and want everything. Help everyone out and streamline things so the kitchen moves faster. Again, not the workers, just the process.
Great to place especially when it’s open on Christmas Day, the cortado was good

Although the food and coffee are delicious, every time I have been to this location I have been ignored at the register for a minimum of 5 minutes. I understand that the store can be busy, but an acknowledgement that I will be addressed soon is appreciated. As I worked in the service industry for many years, this was typically expected.
A variety of seating formats, including large tables. Lots of outlets. Rarely super packed. Very comfortable place for working throughout the day.

Somebody here must really like Post Malone, as one morning I was in there this summer and they played a Post Malone-only playlist for about two hours haha.  Kidding aside, I love how many couches and outlets they have here, it's a very comfortable place to work. Typically not as crowded as some others in the area. Can't speak to the food but I really like the iced coffee.

Such an awesome spot! Great food and drinks - staff is super friendly. It’s my favorite place to work or study from in the area
Great space! Convenient and awesome atmosphere. The coffee is ok, but if you need space to do work, this is a WONDERFUL place

I was in town for business and had an Airbnb across the street from Bru. I was delighted to see they had an extensive menu of smoothies and fresh pressed juices, along with coffee and some food items. I went twice during my trip and both times ordered the flat iron juice (tons of greens) and added CBD for an up-charge. The second time I also ordered an egg sandwich on a croissant with pesto and turkey, and unfortunately that left little to de desired which is the only reason why I’ve deducted a star. The turkey was cold and rubbery and the egg was also cold and overall just not good. The atmosphere is lovely, tons of places to relax and get some work done or catch up with a friend. The juice was delicious and coffees looked good too. I would definitely recommend trying Bru if you’re in the area!

This place is disgusting and the service is terrible.

This place is awesome!!! I ordered banana Nutella crape, it's delicious!!! Also I tried apple caramel cider first time there, I love it!!!  Stuff is really friendly and helpful! Definitely will come again!  Thank you!!!  P.S. the atmosphere there is really warm!!

Such a cute place!!

I cant understand why it would take 20 minutes to make a croissant sandwich that normally should take about 5 minutes, 10 minutes tops if youre very busy (which it very much wasnt. I often come here to draw and enjoy the atmosphere, and it’s a great place to get work done. It is a comfortable, cozy atmosphere with delicious food. The California Crepe is a must!
Service was very slow. Food and coffee were disappointing. Flies were also crawling all over the coffee syrups that had the lids left open.

Conveniently located in the middle of wicker park.  I prefer their delicious coffee options like iced Mexican chocolate, turmeric hot latte and lavender infused latte.  The place has a soothing hipster vibe and you'll see a lot students studying here with their phones and laptops plugged in because there are couches, plentiful work stations and electronic outlets scattered everywhere.   Staff is quiet and efficient but the raw juices here are sort of hot or miss because not all the servers here are the best at juicing the best tasting juices.  I know they serve sandwiches, smoothies and salads here too including outstanding chocolate chip muffins.   I wish they knew how to serve better tasting raw juices though considering the raw juice here is expensive.   People come here to relax, get a drink and charge their laptops up.
Good fresh juice, made on the spot. Would be 5 stars but the guy serving had no personality.
I got a juice, it was good.. but the place is messy, the service was slow and not so friendly.
Strong coffee and plenty of seating. Loads of space to bring a laptop and work. The window seats at the front are a great people watching perch.
Excellent customer service with a nice ambiance. Juices are delicious and healthy.
The employee that helped me out 5/9/18 around 4:40pm was friendly, courteous, & fast. The place is cute. I would definitely come back.

I want to give Bru the benefit of the doubt.. that more often than not their space is much tidier and more put together.. but on this specific Saturday afternoon the place was messy. Upon walking in, there were posters on the floor. The common areas needed a sweeping and a wipe down. The bathroom floor was messy, there was no paper towel and the air dryer was broken (barely blowing warm air) thus I had to dry my hands on my clothes. We ordered two iced coffees and they were only able to make us one before they ran out. It was 4pm. We also ordered a turkey club and it was actually really good and healthy. The side was a bag of chips and it took the employees ten minutes to bring the chips to us after we got our sandwich. I did enjoy the comfy furniture and the many electric outlets. Seems like a good alternative to study or write in a crowded Wicker Park neighborhood. I plan on visiting again in the near future though if I have another subpar experience I will probably never come back.
wonderful place!

We met our wedding photographer here for a planning session this evening.  Ordered a Chai Tea Latte and an Americano.  They told us they couldn't make either drink because they had removed their espresso machine as they were getting ready to demo the bar (yes, while the shop was open).  A worker even laid a construction tarp over the top of our open cups while we waited for the drinks to prep.  We settled on a drip coffee and a brewed tea as that's all they could offer us.  Next, it's time to pay.  I see they have a $5 minimum on credit cards...no big deal, our drinks rang up to about $8.  I hand the cashier my card and he awkwardly asks me to use cash.  I point out that I've exceeded their posted minimum but it did't seem to make a difference.  Fine, you've now thoroughly guilted me, cash.  Get our drinks and sit down to talk business.  Not two minutes later out come the circular saws and hammers! (no joke)  Every few minutes or so we had to put the brakes on our conversation  while we waited for the sawing and hammering to subside.  There are plenty of places within a blocks walk to get a cup of joe.  Don't waste your money here.

Friends and I were in Chicago a  couple of months ago and tried this place for breakfast. Coffee and food were underwhelming; service was just OK. So imagine my surprise when I get an email from them , asking whether I would recommend them or not, that indicated that they had an almost 5 star rating based on 90 reviews! I clicked "no, thanks", and was whisked off to a page asking how they could improve their experience. Just out of curiosity I tried "yes" on the email as well, and was brought to Google Reviews. Sneaky. So, keep in mind that you're getting a very selectively chosen subset of opinions on this place. Take a look at other review sites (assuming the same tactics aren't being used to enhance ratings there too) before you choose this establishment.
